Sandlapper:  native South Carolinians.  Someone from South Carolina.  Upon visiting Columbia/Lancaster, SC, in 1791 George Washington dubbed the people living on the sands near the river shores as "sandlappers."  The state fondly adopted the term to describe all South Carolinians.